Humans as replicator and distributor of viral infections should definitely be studied by investigators who focus on the physiological and epidemiological aspects of the outbreak. Seasonal change in human behaviors, such as individuals being closer together, or changes in diets, and physiological response to environmental change have been presented as possible effectors. [
